<table border="0" width="570">
  <tr>
    <td><p ALIGN="CENTER"><strong><font size="2">COUNTRY AND CITY PEOPLE - SAME RIGHTS AND
    NEEDS IN SPORT</font></strong></p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER"><font size="2">S.Dragutinovic, Z.Zivanovic </font></p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER"><font size="2">Faculty for Science and Mathematics, Kragujevac,<br>
    Faculty of Physical Culture, Belgrade,<br>
    Yugoslavia</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">It is hard to say how many people live in rural areas
    nowadays. In the past, agricultural population was more numerous (50% and more), but life
    in the country, with more obligations and difficulties, was considerably different from
    the convenient life in urban areas. This has caused migrations from the country into the
    cities. With a wish to have an &quot;easier and better&quot; life, familiar situation is
    left behind, and life is continued in a city, with many adaptation problem. However, today
    we can notice that people tend &quot;go back&quot;. A lot of work is to be done by
    sociology demography researches.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">We are interested in the degree of influence of sport
    and recreation (its existence and accessibility) on the migrations from country to the
    cities. Our experience and data show that it considerably influences the wish to change
    place of living due to easier work and better pastimes.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">There are also theories that going in for sport is not
    necessary, or is less necessary, for people in the country. The reason for this is not
    knowing the real role and importance of physical culture. As proof for this statement, the
    following state was registered on the sampie of 3790 young people</font></p>
    <div align="left"><table border="0">
      <tr>
        <td align="left"></td>
        <td align="center"><font size="2">country</font></td>
        <td align="center"><font size="2">city</font></td>
